<item>
            <title>[SPR-2915] getAsText method for a CustomPropertyEditor not called with &lt;form&gt; tag</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2915</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am using the (relatively) new &amp;lt;form&amp;gt; tags, but having the problem that my getAsText() method is not called on my CustomPropertyEditor. However, the setAsText() method gets called fine! I also know the value persists properly because if I change back from a &amp;lt;form&amp;gt; tag to the &amp;lt;spring:bind&amp;gt; tags, it works again (I should clarify that the &amp;lt;spring:bind&amp;gt; tag was not using the getAsText() method either, I was performing comparision by retrieving the id and comparing it directly). This is a snippet from my jsp:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;form:select path=&quot;paymentMethod.type&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;form:option value=&quot;&quot; label=&quot;&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;form:options items=&quot;$&lt;/p&gt;
{paymentMethodTypes}
&lt;p&gt;&quot; itemValue=&quot;id&quot; itemLabel=&quot;name&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/form:select&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;form:errors path=&quot;paymentMethod.type&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;paymentMethodTypes is a list of all possible PaymentMethodTypes. The list populates fine, but the matching value is never &apos;selected&apos; from the list, so it is as if no selection is made.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
