                            <comment id="21218" author="joerg.heinicke@gmx.de" created="Tue, 5 Dec 2006 23:43:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The actual problem is that custom editors do not get applied to the reference data objects or whereever you retrieve paymentMethodTypes from: &lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=31464&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=31464&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21251" author="joerg.heinicke@gmx.de" created="Thu, 7 Dec 2006 10:05:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please have a look at the thread at &lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?p=89477&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?p=89477&lt;/a&gt; for a discussion about this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21252" author="joerg.heinicke@gmx.de" created="Thu, 7 Dec 2006 10:05:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wanted to have the thread, not the post: &lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=32196&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=32196&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21631" author="tortuga" created="Thu, 4 Jan 2007 11:28:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is date formatting possible without the form tags using getAsText()? Since date formatting is locale specific, it should be a render issue, so should be in getAsText(). I&apos;d rather not have to pass locale information to the .jsp page if that is the preferred way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21897" author="tortuga" created="Tue, 23 Jan 2007 11:41:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This actually seems to be working fine as of Spring 2.0.2. I noticed some configuration errors, and my customPropertyEditor wasn&apos;t being registered on render (I&apos;m using Spring Web Flow). With configuration done right, both setAsText() and getAsText() are being called. Was anything changed? If not, then this issue is invalid.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="22198" author="springboy" created="Mon, 12 Feb 2007 09:03:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Tor&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mmm, I am unaware of any changes being made explicitly to address this issue. In line with your comment that it seems to be working, I am closing this issue as &apos;Fixed&apos; for now... just reopen it if required.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;br/&gt;
Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="31158" author="kmapte" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2008 03:09:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi&lt;br/&gt;
I am using Spring 2.5 and when I call the beanwrapper.getPropertyValue the getAsText method does not get called. &lt;br/&gt;
Also looked at the code for TypeDelgate there is no reference to getAsText.&lt;br/&gt;
Which class references the getAsText method? I do not see a way where I can tell to call the getAsText&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please advice&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="31165" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2008 05:52:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;BeanWrapper.getPropertyValue is not defined to return text values. Effectively, only a BindingResult returned by a DataBinder provides such getAsText translation when calling getFieldValue there...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
